      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Combine shredded cooked chicken with barbecue sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper in a bowl; taste and adjust seasoning.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Brush each flatbread lightly with olive oil on the top side, then place them on a baking sheet (or keep in skillet) and pre-toast for 2–3 minutes until just starting to crisp.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Evenly distribute the barbecue chicken mixture over each flatbread, leaving a small border, then sprinkle shredded mozzarella and cheddar evenly over the top and scatter thinly sliced red onion.",
        "time_min": 4
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Return flatbreads to the oven and broil on high (or cover skillet with lid and increase heat) until cheese is melted and edges are browned, about 4–6 minutes. Watch closely to prevent burning.",
